@NODE Introduction "Introduction"

This is a script that converts images given on the command line to a
certain resolution and color depth using one of the following programs:

- ArtEffect2:   tested with version 2.6, 3 and 4
- PPaint:       tested with version 6.4 and 7.x, extra support for 7.x
- Photogenics2: tested with version 2b, not supposed to work with
                Photogenics NG as it does not have ARexx support
- ImageMagick:  Tested with ImageMagick 5.5.5 from
                http://us.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/amiga/ImageMagick-5.5.5.lha
                (ported by Diego Casorran)

It is used mainly for converting a whole bunch of images in one go.

I use it with Directory Opus Magellan. You can use it with any other file
manager - not that Opus isn't just a file manager anymore ;-) - that
allows flexible configuration.

I have written it for the purpose of converting the pictures of themes to
a format that Opus can easily load via common picture datatypes for
AmigaOS.

@ENDNODE

